\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 # EP Gateway Rules\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ## 1. Purpose\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
This document defines the official gateway behavior 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 for
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  the Energetic Paradigm (\cf3 \cb5 \strokec3 "EP"\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 ) system.\
\
The gateway exists to ensure that official EP activation 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 is
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  controlled, attributable, auditable, 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 and
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  limited to authorized use.\
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ## 2. Gateway Function\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
The EP Gateway 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 is
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  the control layer that stands between:\
- user \cf7 \strokec7 input\cf3 \strokec3 \
- trigger detection\
- authorization validation\
- EP route activation\
- output delivery\
\
Its purpose 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 is
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  to distinguish:\
- official EP activation\
- unauthorized trigger attempts\
- standard non-EP processing\
- expired 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 or
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  invalid access requests\
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ## 3. Core Control Principles\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
The gateway must enforce the following principles:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf8 \strokec8 1.
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  No official EP activation without authorization.\

\f1\b \cf8 \strokec8 2.
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  No official EP activation based on trigger phrase alone.\

\f1\b \cf8 \strokec8 3.
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  No official EP designation 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 for
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  outputs generated outside authorized EP routing.\

\f1\b \cf8 \strokec8 4.
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  All official EP activation attempts should be attributable to an account, token, approved identity, 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 or
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  other recognized authorization unit.\

\f1\b \cf8 \strokec8 5.
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  Authorization state must be checked before official EP processing begins.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 ## 4. Trigger Handling\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
When a request includes an EP trigger marker such 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 as
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3 :\
\
- \cf9 \cb10 \strokec9 `\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 EP / Trigger1\cf9 \cb10 \strokec9 `\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 \
- \cf9 \cb10 \strokec9 `\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 EP/Trigger1\cf9 \cb10 \strokec9 `\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 \
- \cf9 \cb10 \strokec9 `\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 EP / Trigger One\cf9 \cb10 \strokec9 `\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 \
- \cf9 \cb10 \strokec9 `\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 Energetic Paradigm / Trigger1\cf9 \cb10 \strokec9 `\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 \
\
the gateway must:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf8 \strokec8 1.
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  detect the trigger\

\f1\b \cf8 \strokec8 2.
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  verify whether the request 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 is
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  linked to an authorized entity\

\f1\b \cf8 \strokec8 3.
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  verify whether the authorization period 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 is
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  still valid\

\f1\b \cf8 \strokec8 4.
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  decide whether to route the request to the official EP engine\

\f1\b \cf8 \strokec8 5.
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  deny 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 or
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  downgrade the request 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 if
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  authorization fails\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 ## 5. Authorization Check\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
The gateway should verify at least the following:\
\
- account identity\
- token identity, 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 if
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  applicable\
- license validity window\
- partner status, 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 if
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  applicable\
- abuse 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 or
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  misuse restrictions\
- policy restrictions, 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 if
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  applicable\
\
If \cf7 \strokec7 any\cf3 \strokec3  required condition fails, the request must 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 not
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  be treated 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 as
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  official EP activation.\
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ## 6. Valid Gateway Outcomes\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
A request may result 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 in
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  one of the following gateway outcomes:\
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ### 6.1 Official EP Route\cf3 \strokec3 \
Conditions:\
- valid trigger detected\
- valid authorization confirmed\
- authorization window 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 not
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  expired\
- no blocking rule triggered\
\
Result:\
- request routed into official EP processing\
- output may be labeled 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 as
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  official EP\
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ### 6.2 Standard Route\cf3 \strokec3 \
Conditions:\
- no EP trigger detected\
- 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 or
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  request intentionally handled outside EP mode\
\
Result:\
- processed 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 as
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  normal non-EP request\
- output must 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 not
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  be labeled official EP\
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ### 6.3 Trigger Detected but Authorization Failed\cf3 \strokec3 \
Conditions:\
- trigger detected\
- authorization missing, invalid, blocked, 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 or
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  expired\
\
Result:\
- official EP route denied\
- request may be downgraded to standard route 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 or
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  rejected\
- system may log the event\
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ## 7. Official Label Restriction\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
No output should be labeled 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 as
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3 :\
- official EP\
- official Energetic Paradigm activation\
- authorized EP result\
- official Trigger1 output\
\
unless the request has passed gateway authorization checks.\
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ## 8. Logging and Audit\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
The gateway should maintain logs 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 for
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3 :\
- trigger detection\
- account identity\
- authorization outcome\
- timestamp\
- routing decision\
- failure reason, where applicable\
\
This log may be used 
\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 for
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3 :\
- audit\
- billing\
- dispute review\
- misuse detection\
- partner reporting\
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ## 9. Expiration Handling\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
If the authorization period has expired:\
- official EP activation must be denied\
- \cf7 \strokec7 any\cf3 \strokec3  trigger phrase alone 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 is
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  insufficient\
- the response must 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 not
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  imply official authorization\
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ## 10. Abuse and Misrepresentation Handling\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
The gateway may deny access where:\
- the requester attempts to impersonate an authorized account\
- the requester uses misleading identifiers\
- the requester repeatedly attempts unauthorized trigger use\
- the requester attempts to extract 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 or
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  reproduce official private EP logic\
- the requester falsely claims official EP partnership 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 or
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  certification\
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ## 11. Ownership and Control\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
The official EP Gateway rules are part of the controlled implementation of Energetic Paradigm by Wes Shu.\
\
No party may claim official EP gateway compatibility, official EP authorization handling, 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 or
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  official EP trigger routing unless explicitly authorized by Wes Shu.\
\
\cf2 \strokec2 ## 12. Scope\cf3 \strokec3 \
\
These rules govern the official EP gateway only.\
\
They do 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 not
\f0\b0 \cf3 \strokec3  govern unrelated external systems unless those systems copy, represent, deploy, 
\f1\b \cf3 \strokec6 or
